<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1591,1796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Comments: 
<bibRefCitation author="Champion" box="[287,484,1591,1615]" firstAuthor="Champion" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 416" refId="ref34673" refString="Champion, G. C. (1898 - 1901) Hemiptera-Heteroptera. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Rhynchota, 2, 1 - 416." type="journal article" year="1898">Champion (1898)</bibRefCitation>
affirmed seeing 
<specimenCount box="[672,797,1591,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens from PE that appeared to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Champion, 1898)" baseAuthorityName="Champion" baseAuthorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Tachygerris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrilineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">T. quadrilineatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion" box="[256,450,1628,1652]" firstAuthor="Champion" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 416" refId="ref34673" refString="Champion, G. C. (1898 - 1901) Hemiptera-Heteroptera. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Rhynchota, 2, 1 - 416." type="journal article" year="1898">Champion, 1898</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This is the only record of the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[970,1041,1628,1652]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and here is considered erroneous, probably corresponding to some of the other species reported for the country. 
<bibRefCitation author="Drake and Harris" box="[1017,1290,1663,1687]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="179 - 241" refId="ref36685" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1934) The Gerrinae of the Western Hemisphere (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 23, 179 - 241." type="journal article" year="1934">Drake and Harris (1934)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[305,410,1700,1724]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, which is also a very suspicious record, and not considered valid here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Drake and Harris" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="179 - 241" refId="ref36685" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1934) The Gerrinae of the Western Hemisphere (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 23, 179 - 241." type="journal article" year="1934">Drake and Harris (1934)</bibRefCitation>
probably mistakenly mentioned 
<collectingCountry box="[594,698,1736,1760]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
instead of 
<collectingCountry box="[822,914,1736,1759]" name="Panama" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Panama</collectingCountry>
, a country where the occurrence of the species is expected, considering its known distribution from 
<collectingCountry box="[742,828,1772,1796]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[863,989,1772,1796]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
